She says although there is a decline of HIV infected people in the country, young people remain vulnerable and exposed to the disease. Ncube Nkomo says young people need to practice healthy sexual choices. According to statistics, young people between the age of 15 and 24 are at high risk of getting infected. Ncube Nkomo says since 1999, the Love Life initiative has been resourceful in assisting young people in South Africa.

--Bomkazi Malobola--


